data.title: Our Experienced Providers
data.meta_description: Primary Care Associates of Wichita, KS offers primary care for all ages, from birth to death. Our staff is dedicated to happily helping you live a healthy life! Call us to schedule an appointment today at (316) 684-2851.
data.text:
Kelsey Gilliam was born and raised in Wichita and the surrounding area. She graduated from Rose Hill High School, then attended Hutchinson Community College on a basketball scholarship, while completing her prerequisite nursing courses. Kelsey attended Bethel College in North Newton, Kansas where she graduated in 2016 with her Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree. With a love to work in a time critical and fast paced environment, she developed a passion for Emergency Nursing. Kelsey continued her education and after two years, in 2021 she graduated with her Master of Science in Nursing-Family Nurse Practitioner degree from the University of Missouri-Kansas City.

After graduation, Kelsey began working in Cardiology, managing acute and chronic illness in the hospital and clinical settings. Kelsey later transitioned into a rapid paced urgent care, treating a variety of medical illnesses. With a desire to create meaningful relationships with patients of all ages, she is excited to further her career with Primary Care Associates.

Kelsey met her husband, Austin while working as a nurse in the Emergency Department and he as a Firefighter in Emporia, Kansas. Kelsey and Austin reside in Wichita and Austin proudly serves on the Wichita Fire Department. Together, they enjoy raising their daughter Palmer. In Kelseyâ€™s free time, she enjoys being outdoors, spending time with family and friends, and she has a love for warm chocolate chip cookies.

Annie Dang is a board certified physician assistant and grew up in Wichita, Kansas. She is a graduate of Kapaun Mt. Carmel High School. She obtained her Bachelors of Science degree at Newman University in 2019, then went on to complete her PA studies at Wichita State University. She has previous experience in Infectious Diseases, managing acute illnesses in the hospital.

In her free time, she loves to travel and discover good food, practice taekwondo, and play pickleball.

I grew up in Wichita, KS, and feel very blessed to be able to practice in my home town where I am close to my family and friends. Growing up, I love being around people and science was always fascinating to me so it was very natural for me to lean towards healthcare. I started my professional career as a Medical Technologist and Clinical Laboratory Scientist. After ten years of performing labs and managing a laboratory, I decided to go back to school to become a Physician Assistant. This transition allowed me to be in direct patient care, to help treat, manage, and more importantly build relationships with patients. It is a true honor and privilege for me to take care of patients and what is most important to them, their families. I look forward to being part of your healthcare team!
